parameter.description:
The facility actions supported by this VoiceService.  {{enum}}
The list MAY include vendor-specific Facility Actions, which MUST use the format defined in {{bibref|TR-106}}.
Facility Actions are referenced in the VoiceService data model in the objects {{object|.CallControl.NumberingPlan.{i}.PrefixInfo.{i}.}} and {{object|.Terminal.{i}.ButtonMap.Button.{i}.}}.

Identifier of the type of codec. {{enum}}
The parameter MAY instead be a vendor-specific codec, which MUST be in the format defined in {{bibref|TR-106}}.  For example:
"X_EXAMPLE-COM_MyCodec"

SIP network with which this SIP client is associated.
{{reference}}
This parameter can only be modified if {{param|Origin}} is {{enum|Static|Origin}}.

The tone to be played to the user when the SIP response is received.
{{reference}}
{{empty}} indicates no tone is to be played for this event.

SIP client or ISDN interface associated with the identities represented by this trunk.
{{reference}}
This parameter can only be modified if {{param|Origin}} is {{enum|Static|Origin}}.

Party originating the call.
{{reference}}
{{object|.Trunk}}, {{object|.SIP.Registrar.{i}.Account}} and {{object|.SIP.Client}} objects SHOULD be referenced only when {{object|.Interwork}} is in use.

Destination party of the call.
{{reference}}
{{object|.Trunk}}, {{object|.SIP.Registrar.{i}.Account}} and {{object|.SIP.Client}} objects SHOULD be only referenced only when {{object|.Interwork}} is in use.

The {{object|.CallControl.Line}} used to process the call.
{{reference}}
When {{object|.Interwork}} is in use, this parameter is {{empty}}.

{{list}} {{reference}}
For an incoming call multiple {{object|.CallControl.Extension}} objects can be involved till one user answers the call.
When {{object|.Interwork}} is in use, this parameter is {{empty}}.

The {{object}} for the next phase of the tone pattern, after the specified {{param|Duration}} of this phase has completed.
{{reference}}
{{empty}} indicates that the tone pattern is to terminate after the current phase is completed.

The description for the tone to be associated with the given event.
{{reference}}
{{empty}} indicates no tone is to be played for this event.

The {{object}} for the next phase of the ring pattern, after the specified {{param|Duration}} of this phase has completed.
{{reference}}
{{empty}} indicates that the ring pattern is to terminate after the current phase is completed.
